description: Good looking bankers and CEOs earn $1million more on average than their less attractive counterparts - despite the fact they may not be working as hard.

title: Kate has done a third of her royal engagements within 12 miles of her home in Windsor Castle
description: An analysis by The Mail on Sunday can reveal that almost a third of her working days - 18 out of 61 - since assuming her title in September were within 12 miles of Adelaide Cottage.

title: Kouri Richins Googled 'luxury prisons for the rich' after allegedly murdering husband
description: Kouri Richins, the Moscow Mule 'killer' who wrote a book for children about coping with grief after her husband's death, reportedly googled 'luxury prisons for the rich' after his murder.

title: Three teenagers charged over western Sydney Tregear home death
description: An 18-year-old male has been charged with murder and two other teens, a male and a female, face assault charges after a 32-year-old man's body was found in a western Sydney house on Saturday night.

title: Proposed California bill would brand parents 'abusive' if they refuse to affirm their child's gender
description: A proposed amendment to a bill in California would classify parents who refuse to  affirm their child's gender as abusive and could result in revoked custody.

title: Donald Trump claims he has FIVE THOUSAND prosecutors after him
description: Donald Trump complained of his continued legal plights, exaggerating to a crowd in North Carolina that there are 5,000 prosecutors pursuing him, and that he 'sort of enjoys' the attacks.

title: Pigeon lady of Pyrmont keeps birds in her backpack, says the 'rats with wings' make ideal pets
description: Times might be tough in Sydney's biggest city, but not for two pampered pigeons, Walter and Charlie, who after their morning air shower, infrared therapy and ionic treatment, visit the CBD.

title: EMILY PRESCOTT: Princess Kate has a secret body double at Chelsea boutique Catherine Walker
description: EMILY PRESCOTT: The Princess of Wales (pictured) is such a valued customer for Catherine Walker that I hear she even has her own bespoke mannequin at the label's Chelsea boutique.

title: Trans influencer Dylan Mulvaney shows off stunning new platinum hairdo in 90s-style black dress
description: Brunette-born Dylan Mulvaney has seemingly taken the Bud Light criticism in her stride and has continued to post on social media - and now she's showed off her new blonde transformation.

title: Father jailed over fraud and drugs cannot be deported back to Jamaica
description: Swaye BInns, 45, will remain in the UK after he set up an illegal business in Croydon as an immigration tribunal was told three of his children were 'in and out prison'.

title: Erling Haaland celebrates with girlfriend Isabel Johansen after Champions League win
description: Johansen had watched the final from the stands alongside Haaland's father Alf-Inge, with both pictured at the Ataturk Olympic Stadium wearing Man City kits.

title: Bargain hunting shoppers are switching supermarkets to hunt for better deals
description: A study has shown that 14 million Brits have swapped where they do their weekly shop in the past year, and that switching saves the average person around £756.

title: As Vanity Fair's ex-editor blasts Harry and Meghan, Christopher Wilson reviews the facts
description: CHRISTOPHER WILSON sets out 20 things Harry and Meghan have done which prove former Vanity Fair editor Graydon Carter right that they have 'made every wrong move you can possibly make'.

title: MAIL ON SUNDAY COMMENT: Boris is a tiger undone by 'minuscule nibbling mice'
description: MAIL ON SUNDAY COMMENT: The greatest issue at stake in the treatment of Boris Johnson is the lack of democracy.

title: Labour is accused of 'sabotaging' the Government's plans to house migrants on barges
description: Tory Party Deputy Chairman Lee Anderson has accused Labour of sabotaging the Government's plan to house asylum seekers on barges amid further rejection of the plans.

title: Manchester City were once branded a 'joke' but now lead the way on and off the pitch
description: ROB DRAPER AT THE ATATURK STADIUM: The sniggers were not just emanating from Old Trafford when the press release went out in August 2008. All over Europe, football was sceptical.

title: Inside Man City's Champions League party: Jack Grealish sings while drinking a beer
description: Manchester City players and staff have got their Champions League celebrations underway in Istanbul after victory over Istanbul landed them a first European title and the fabled Treble.

title: Darlinghurst bus stabbing: Teenager charged after commuter allegedly knifed
description: A teenager has been charged with stabbing a stranger on a bus in broad daylight.

title: Elderly woman is killed after being hit by a car in Sydney's north
description: An elderly woman has died after she was struck by a vehicle while walking in Roseville in Sydney's north.

title: Ex-wife of Syrian refugee who stabbed six warned  authorities about him months earlier
description: The Mail on Sunday can reveal Abdalmasih Hanoun's Swedish wife warned French and Swiss authorities about her husband months before the attack, but she was ignored.

title: Two-thirds of workers believe female leaders are better than their male counterparts
description: Female leaders were perceived as excelling men in key leadership areas such as multi-tasking, while 83% of employees viewed female bosses as more empathetic.

title: Teachers at Britain's oldest school will go on strike for the first time in its 1,425-year history
description: Bosses at King's School in Canterbury which was founded in 597AD say they are 'disappointed' staff are set to walk out next week in a row over pensions.

title: 'Needless' limit on what charity lotteries can raise could cost good causes £200m
description: People's Postcode Lottery, which supports more than 70 major charities, believes it could hand out an extra £198 million if the Government slashed the red tape on ticket sales.

title: Gen Z daters are more likely to admit to cheating on exes when on a first date, study shows
description: Researchers found that eight out of 10 people own up if they have a history of cheating on previous partners - in the hope of getting their new relationship off to a good start.

title: Cleverly faces Tory backlash over plans to visit China with warnings some ministers could RESIGN
description: Mr Cleverly has angered Tories by arguing that Britain should adopt a less critical stance towards the country, on the grounds that isolating China would be against the UK's national interest.

title: BBC plans to make sure new recruits have 'diverse opinions' after claims of 'liberal bias'
description: Senior figures hosted talks on changes which could be made to the recruitment process to make sure the BBC hires staff with a differing range of views.

title: Launderettes could be sent spinning into history as experts warn of high energy prices
description: In their heyday, there were about 14,000 launderettes in the UK, with their importance to communities reflected by scriptwriters for BBC soap opera EastEnders.

title: ITV bosses 'offer to pay for counselling' for This Morning employees over Phillip Schofield scandal
description: The mental health care, for Willoughby among others, comes after the TV host addressed viewers last week following Schofield's admittance of an affair with a young male runner on the show.

title: Shire horse Sammy adopted two thoroughbred foals after losing her baby
description: At a month old, Mouse and Tracey are thriving and Sammy struggles to keep up - but that's hardly surprising. Both foals were bred from thoroughbred racehorses and Sammy is not their biological mother.
